frameDefinitions: An Item changes its physical size.
A person (Speaker) expresses a Message or mental content, broadly understood, in a particular Manner.
A person, the Cognizer, thinks about a Topic over a period of time.
This frame contains nouns denoting Aggregates of Individuals.
This frame has to do with scientific taxonomy.
This frame is concerned with the sounds produced by animate entities by means of their vocal tracts.
frameExamples: The pile of leaves had <t>shrunk</t> by about half after the first haul.
The men were silently <t>mulling</t> <t>over</t> the proposition of committing an assassination
An <t><fex name='Agg'>army</fex></t> of postal workers descended on my office.
<t><fex name='Rank'>Phylum</fex></t> Arthropoda contains crustaceans, insects, spiders and other creepy-crawlies.
He woke up because of the <t>cries</t> of the crows outside.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the <fen>Item</fen> whose size changes.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the expansion occurs.
<fen>Speaker</fen>, the person who encodes the <fen>Message</fen>, occurs as the External Argument of all the verbs:
The <fen>Message</fen> is almost invariably expressed in an NP Object. (The only exceptions occur with the verb <t>express</t>, which is occasionally used with that-clause complements.)

For most of the words in this frame, some expression of <fen>Manner</fen> or <fen>Medium</fen> is obligatory. As in other frames, <fen>Manner</fen> expressions characterize the action (in this case, the speech act performed by the <fen>Speaker</fen>). However, a wide range of <fen>Manner</fen> expressions occurs in this frame, including the following types:
<fen>Medium</fen> expresses the <fen>Medium</fen> of communication, such as the language used or the specific type of text in which the <fen>Message</fen> occurs:
With a target verb, the Cognizer is usually expressed as an External Argument, with the Topic appearing as an Object NP, a gerundive verbal Complement, or a PP.
With a target verb, the <fen>Topic</fen> is usually expressed as an Object NP, a gerundive verbal complement, or a PP.
The time at which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> considers the <fen>Topic</fen>.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that are the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
The <fen>Rank</fen> is the taxonomic category to which the <fen>Member</fen> belongs.  It is also always the target-denoting noun.
The living organism which belongs to the expressed <fen>Rank</fen>.
An entity that is construed as a single point source emitting sound.

The location at which sound is produced. This role differs from <fen>Location_of_sound_source</fen> in that it does not highlight the sound's spreading from its source to the perceiver's location, which is usually indicated by the preposition 'from'.

A <fex><t>crowd</t></fex> of hoodlums filled the plaza.
Molds and mushrooms belong to the <fex>kingdom</fex> Fungi.
Do humans belong to the order <fex>Primate</fex>?
He woke up because of the cries <fex>of the crows outside</fex>.
The hiss of snakes <fex>outside the tent</fex> was a constant source of worry.
